 However, gold data labelled by expert annotators suggest that maximizing the probability of a single sense may not be the most suitable training objective for WSD, especially if the sense inventory of choice is fine-grained.
 In this paper, we approach WSD as a multi-label classification problem in which multiple senses can be assigned to each target word.
